Comment: 0,0:20:24.77,0:20:24.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.71,0:20:34.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable Romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.24,0:20:37.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.70,0:20:41.42,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.42,0:20:44.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.55,0:20:55.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.97,0:20:59.73,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.73,0:21:03.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.27,0:21:06.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.11,0:21:09.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.69,0:21:13.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.24,0:21:17.79,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.79,0:21:21.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.49,0:21:27.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.14,0:21:30.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams: {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.55,0:21:34.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.18,0:21:36.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.00,0:21:41.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.77,0:21:45.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, I'll do my best to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:48.77,0:21:48.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.66,0:00:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,After realizing they are actually blood-related twins, \NLuise and Lotte became so close,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as to the point of their hearts beating in unison. {lit: two hearts started shaking; shake; jolt; jolting; vibration; tremor; flickering}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.86,0:00:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"I wish to meet my dad."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.57,0:00:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"I want to meet my mom."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.22,0:00:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The result has been a plan \Nof unthinkable magnitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.80,0:00:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise as Lotte, and Lotte as Luise - \Nthey will swap places to this way return home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.35,0:00:30.38,Sign,,0,0,110,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8}Episode 4 \N {\fs45} Onset of the Operation {作戦開始} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} Translation: Perevodildo    |    Timings: Sub-RoRo   \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.59,0:00:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.28,0:01:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What a waste. \NTook a lot of effort to make this photo. {actually "[we] put so much effort into this commemorative photo"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.63,0:01:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But keeping it would mean \Nrisking to blow the gaff. {/if it's discovered, our secret would leak}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.54,0:01:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Before long, we'll be able to take a new one, \Neven better picture. I promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.62,0:01:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How should we stay in touch?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.25,0:01:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we'll have to stick to letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.08,0:01:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A General Delivery would do. {Poste restante, also known as general delivery in North American English, is a service where the post office holds the mail until the recipient calls for it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.00,0:01:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day, on our way home from school \Nwe'll be checking if there's any post for us. {/whether or not it came}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.76,0:01:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But for how long?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.03,0:01:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How about we start with one month?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.10,0:01:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After one month, we'll arrange a rendezvous \Nto decide our further course of action. {/we'll meet somewhere to decide what happens next}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.76,0:01:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope, by then we know enough \Nto unravel the mystery of their parting. {lit: until then it'll be good to learn many things - no clue what she means, taking from book}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.74,0:02:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.73,0:02:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor little soul Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.81,0:02:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's show her our support. {lit is "to be helpful; to be dependable; to stand by (someone)​" and idk what it means}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.20,0:02:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.66,0:02:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Luise, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.98,0:02:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.09,0:02:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! Gloom is unbecoming of a girl. {/you're not cheerful at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.29,0:02:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At a time like this, \Neasier said than done.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.19,0:02:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, my soul is empty, \Nand somehow, my belly, too. {lit: somehow can't help my stomach being empty - I can't find this in the book and I think they refer to her being fat and eating away her grief, this was already played around in ep3}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably think I'm weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.93,0:02:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing of the kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.02,0:02:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,However, overeating is also insalubrious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.34,0:02:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My, would you look at who is being admonitory! {lit: you can't speak for others, unsure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.99,0:02:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember, when I first arrived here, \Nsomeone was so mad, she was eating until she bursts. {heartily (eating); devouring; munching; gobbling} {/I wonder who was it ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.78,0:02:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wasn't really eating to the point of bursting!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.18,0:02:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not eating! It was gobbling so vigorous, \NI thought you'd swallow the spoon, too! {lit: was not eating (no clue what it means), you had enough power to eat a plate, too} {it doesn't help that we never saw her doing it in anime and it's only described in the book}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.40,0:02:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the memory of it is still amusing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.45,0:02:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the point. \NStill think you're weird? {sonna hen datta? this was weird? no clue what she means and also what stephie's answer means}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:03:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You both suddenly felt unwell \Nand want a leave from swimming? {I think she means they swim every day on a schedule}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.02,0:03:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.81,0:03:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess your mental link is strong. {close (e.g. relationship); intimate - I think she here rather explains that they felt this simultaneously because they are close}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.64,0:03:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well, you can spend this afternoon \Ngetting a good rest in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.70,0:03:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.79,0:03:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it's okay? \NThey are clearly feigning it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.26,0:03:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Those girls only have one week left \Nbefore they have to part ways again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.04,0:03:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You've no idea how much those two \Nneed to talk over in that short a time. {/they want to talk about a million things right now}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.49,0:03:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be entering the water so suddenly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to warm up first! {/do warm-up exercises properly}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.82,0:03:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.80,0:03:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's get to learning. {/study}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.98,0:04:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the layout of the house. \NMake sure to remember it really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.79,0:04:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You can trust our servant Resi \Nto tend to all the housekeeping work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But you should always be on the alert with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.02,0:04:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.14,0:04:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi is a big fat liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.69,0:04:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What she says and what she does \Nare two different things. {she prolly refers to this from book: In doing so she noticed two things: first, that Rosa the\Nhousekeeper had made a mistake on practically every page,\Nand second, that every one of these mistakes was to Rosa's advantage. - embezzlement or idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.12,0:04:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And dad still hasn't noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.83,0:04:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Men are some very oblivious creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.50,0:04:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.08,0:04:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, this looks like a spacious and gorgeous house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.57,0:04:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but where's the dad's working office?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.91,0:04:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,His atelier is elsewhere. {/his ... is in another place}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.55,0:04:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He rents a room along Kärntner Ring​ \Nexpressly for that purpose. {Darkonius — Today at 07:03\NI don't remember the book very well, but I assume this is in reference to the Ringstraße in Vienna, a section of which is known as the Kärntner Ring (after the Kärntner Straße).\NThe various sections of the Ringstraße all have their own names that they're commonly referred to by.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.54,0:04:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me show you the way. You start on Rotenturmstraße, \Npass by St. Stephen's Cathedral, {lit would be something like "from the red tower street (literal translation of Rotenturmstraße), pass by stephan's daijin (no clue, but refers to St. Stephen's Cathedral - 大聖堂), ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.50,0:04:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,after passing by the Opera House, you turn left \Nand find yourself on Kärntner Ring. {lit: turn to left on opera house, Kärntner ring}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.42,0:04:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where his apartment is located. {/he rents one room in apartment on that street - unsure}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.36,0:04:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom works for an illustrated magazine \N"Munich Graph." {/mom's place of work is Munich Illustrated - this is from en ver and like in the last ep, graph is a little meaningless in japanese, but here we hear graph explicitly so can't circumvent it, added "ill. mag." instead to make it clear how a photo ends up there}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.46,0:04:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Their phone number is highlighted in the list \Nright next to the phone. {yoko no is "horisontal" but deepl has it "My phone number is on the list next to the phone." so i think she means "list that is lying on the table in the same plane as phone"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.98,0:04:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Her Editor-in-chief is Doctor Bernau. {ドクトル・ベルナウ}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.41,0:04:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A very hearty old chap. {ojisan, hate it here}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.18,0:04:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can only ever call him \Nwhen it's a matter of life and death!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.65,0:05:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Bernau, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.75,0:05:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom works as an Editor there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.59,0:05:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She chooses topics, sorts out photos \Nand even writes articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.26,0:05:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief puts an infinite confidence in our mom. {/he trust mom completely}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why she is always so busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing. I'm so delighted. \NMy mom is that capable a person!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.34,0:05:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Be mindful, though. There are times when I'm the one \Nhaving to act momly towards her, {/there are times when I'm being more of mom than she is}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.33,0:05:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,like whenever mom throws a tantrum! {lit: sometimes, to be unreasonable; to whine; to throw a tantrum, mom}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.69,0:05:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For real? How peculiar!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.67,0:05:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When this happens, it means she is very tired, \Nso you should react in the most caring manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.70,0:05:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll get better after just one night's sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.80,0:05:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. Got it. Not letting you down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm starting! Get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.15,0:05:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, this will also be on the test. {/now, next is PE time - I think she means "you need to learn to be fit as I am, too"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.42,0:05:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, can we join, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.07,0:05:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Don't you two have something better to do, \Nlike jawjawing to one another? {/don't you wanna do some more gossiping with each other only}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Christine is at it again, like a broken record.\NCome on, let them join!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.23,0:06:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, let them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.31,0:06:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as everyone else is okay with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.14,0:06:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll all good, come on in!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.74,0:06:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.31,0:06:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, everyone. You ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.54,0:06:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going in! Monica!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.28,0:06:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My! Of course I couldn't catch it. \NIt was {\i1}Luise's{\i0} ball. {/I'm no match for ..}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.39,0:06:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive! No way I will ever be able \Nto throw that strong a ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.90,0:06:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.41,0:06:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte is a complete bungler in sports! {/weak in physical activities}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll also have a hard time pretending to be that weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.94,0:06:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing the cooking? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.94,0:06:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.23,0:06:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, cleaning and laundry, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.41,0:06:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally! There's no housekeeping duty \Nout of your reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.16,0:06:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what mom calls me \Nher little housekeeper for!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.07,0:06:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious. No way I do that! {/lies, i cant do that}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.42,0:06:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know how to turn on the gas properly! {/I've never had to ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.32,0:06:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't? {/never}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.32,0:06:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Told you. For that, we always had Resi, the servant. {/it's ...'s job}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.47,0:06:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, see it as an opportunity \Nto learn some new skill for the future. {/if you do it properly, you won't have trouble in the future - no clue what she means, where's louse supposed to learn to do it}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.35,0:06:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Put that in the memo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.29,0:06:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't believe it's actually a thing. {/It wasn't supposed to be like this - unsure}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.18,0:07:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom's favorite dish \Nis beef soup with macaroni. {/macaroni soup with beef}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.96,0:07:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Beef - you buy that from Huber's{ meat shop}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Get half a pound of filet with a lot of marbling. {kanokomadara is pattern of white spots; dapples - i think she refers to the intermuscular fat white flecks, although I also found "A tie-dyed pattern with white spots resembling the back of a baby deer."}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.45,0:07:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Huber, family butcher, corner of Max Emanuel Street \Nand Prince Eugene Street. {this makes no sense, there's no max emmanuel street in munich, but maybe there was one before so w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.61,0:07:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,...corner of Prince Eugene Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.02,0:07:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The cook book is in the kitchen cupboard drawer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.52,0:07:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That book has in it all the recipes I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.15,0:07:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,...kitchen cupboard drawer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.49,0:07:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if Lotte could do something, \Ndoesn't mean I'll ever be able to repeat it. {deepl and google are pretty confident about this meaning even if I don't see how kagiranai makes sense here - not limited to}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.76,0:07:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No excuses! You do everything to the letter. \NWon't make a convincing me otherwise. {/cook properly, you're me after all}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.26,0:07:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, even if I bungle it, I can just say \NI've forgotten how to do it while I was away for vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.16,0:07:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Would do for a plan B. \NAfter all, if things go wrong, you can write me at once. {/if there's something you don't understand, ask me in a letter will you}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.70,0:07:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Omelette...{\i0}\NYour favorite dish is omelette?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.62,0:07:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever we eat at the Imperial Hotel, \NI always ask for multiple refills.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.89,0:07:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad's always so pleased when I eat a lot. {/if you say it's tasty, ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.49,0:07:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Multiple refills?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.08,0:08:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The very thought of eating that slimy omelette \Nmakes my stomach turn over. {lit: for me, inside omelet, slitheringly; wriggling, slipping and sliding​ thing is not one's cup of tea; not one's favorite}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I get away with only eating one? {unsure, maybe she means "I've not eaten it even once"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.36,0:08:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}will{\i0} eat it! \NWon't make a convincing me otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.36,0:08:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I suppose, if you eat four or five refills \Nof omelette on the very first day,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.00,0:08:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you could say you've had enough omelette \Nto last you the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.17,0:08:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.47,0:08:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just why does summer vacation \Nhave to come to an end so soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.38,0:08:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Already on the day after tomorrow, \Nit would be time to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.72,0:08:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after I've made so much good friends here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.89,0:08:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm looking forward \Nto returning to Vienna, because... {/want to return ... sooner}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.85,0:08:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,...you can't live without mama! {yearned for; longed for; missed}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.85,0:08:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Truda, how coarse!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.43,0:08:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,, Sorry, sorry, Monica.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.83,0:08:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd really just prefer \Nto stay here for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.26,0:08:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But the life never stands still. {/you can't not return forever}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.04,0:08:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up. And dive headlong into your new life. {/jump into new everyday}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.95,0:08:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your happiness is our concern, too, Stephie. {/we are cheering; rooting (for); support}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.39,0:08:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I perked up. {/I cheered up}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.94,0:08:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,People! News, news!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.59,0:09:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A big package arrived! {luggage; baggage; package​}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.70,0:09:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A package?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.77,0:09:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell party gifts\Nfrom Brigitte's dad! {/... sent it}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.18,0:09:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A surfeit of big boxes with toys!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.92,0:09:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Also a lot of lanterns, streamers, and the like! {/there are also decorations and other stuff}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.06,0:09:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.52,0:09:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow evening, \Nwe'll have a farewell party!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.77,0:09:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,With a lottery to distribute the presents! {lottery; tombola; drawing}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.64,0:09:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,First prize is roller skates!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.64,0:09:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.54,0:09:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, Lotte, I'm going, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.61,0:09:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A farewell party. \NJust what we need, right? {just right (time, size, length, etc.)​ - I think she means "just what we need to put our strategy to test"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.79,0:09:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's put it to try.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.47,0:09:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If nobody notices, it's a complete success.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.01,0:09:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll make the party a dress rehearsal, \Nbefore returning home this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.49,0:09:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.26,0:10:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Braiding your hair isn't easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.36,0:10:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get used to it, \Nafter doing it every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.61,0:10:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,On my part, it's the ordeal of adjusting my character... {seems a simple sentence but I don't know for the life of it what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.42,0:10:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte, this countenance is nothing like me. {/I don't do that face}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? But you have it all the time, \Nyou just never notice it. {always; all the time; constantly; frequently; often}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.83,0:10:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.27,0:10:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at it! {/see?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.72,0:10:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me introduce myself: Lotte Körner. \NNice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.28,0:10:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I am Luise Palfy. Hey, you! \NA Munich girl who thinks she is the cat's whiskers!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.86,0:10:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it out of character?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.33,0:10:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all. Bull's eye! {/just right}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.65,0:10:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It just feels so peculiar \Nto be watching myself from the side. {/funny/amusing to see it from outside; from the side​}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.26,0:10:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I actually quite like \Nthat exemplary candor of yours. {frank; candid; straightforward; openhearted; direct; outspoken}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.37,0:10:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet if I'm not cautious, \NI might casually let slip what's on my mind. {/suddenly; in a flash; rapidly; nimbly; alertly}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.67,0:10:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting today, we're to swap places \Nalong with our whole lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.57,0:11:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Our names, our belongings, \Nour homes and friends - everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.55,0:11:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.94,0:11:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This apron - I got two of them, \Nso I'll take one with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.19,0:11:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell dad it's a souvenir from a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.65,0:11:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same I was borrowing the other day! {dunno why she says that here}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.87,0:11:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom bought those \Nfor my birthday last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.28,0:11:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,From Oberpollinger's. {from de}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.55,0:11:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A department store on Neuhauserstraße. {, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.54,0:11:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Next to Karlstor. {/Carl's Gate}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.85,0:11:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, it is my most treasured memento. {charm; amulet}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.51,0:11:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as mine. {/for me too}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.00,0:11:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up. {/hold tight}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.25,0:11:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.51,0:11:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure am going to miss you all after today. \NBut at least tonight's farewell party spells fun. {no clue what she means: with everyone, limited to today lonely/yearning/sad}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.11,0:11:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. As soon as we finish the breakfast, \Nwe need to start preparing. {/decorating}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.78,0:11:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder who's going to win the roller skates. {, the first prize}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.75,0:11:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you show a thing you want it real bad, \Nyou shoo away the luck{ of getting it}. {lit: if you're too wistful; desirous of; hungry-looking; greedy-looking, you won't hit it returning home - I think it's some wisdom about how if you want it too much, it'll respond by not hitting you/you'll get in return not receiving it/being chosen by lottery}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.66,0:11:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.00,0:11:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Truda, hold the ladder for me, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.43,0:11:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.86,0:12:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Counselor, let me help you with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.62,0:12:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise? Right, I could use your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.88,0:12:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Climbing on trees is not my thing. {/I don't like high places}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.81,0:12:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Truda. Let's help the others now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.45,0:12:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.08,0:12:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, be careful, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.65,0:12:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.45,0:12:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good start. {/you're getting pretty good}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody has got a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.53,0:12:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, being you just means being reckless. {no clue what she means: by becoming you, frantic; frenetic; desperate/certain death - maybe like "being you is life-threatening" or "I had to become fearless to become you"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.10,0:12:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know I'm just as afraid of the height \Nas Fraulein Ulrica is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.43,0:12:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My knees are shaking like crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.28,0:12:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Breathtaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.41,0:12:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a dream come true! {/beautiful like a dream}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.29,0:12:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember - all of that my papa sent to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.17,0:12:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He runs a department store.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.66,0:13:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's something I like among papa's goods, \NI can get it in a snap of a finger! {/in papa's store, anything I like - he buys it for me}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.53,0:13:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.32,0:13:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Brigitte. Not even Munich girls \Nhave been spared her bragging.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.56,0:13:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But hey, at least Brigitte has one redeeming feature, \Nwhich is her generous papa. {generous; magnanimous; open-handed; liberal}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.73,0:13:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say that again! {unsure what she means それは言えてる}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.11,0:13:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, come join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.69,0:13:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This Punsch is delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.15,0:13:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.08,0:13:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.01,0:13:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.73,0:13:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.46,0:13:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina, did you put any alcohol in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.67,0:13:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not! \NIt's a drink for children.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.12,0:13:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it's strangely intoxicating. {/if felt like I'm drunk}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.17,0:13:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm feeling so much livelier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.09,0:13:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luise, are you doing it this year, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.37,0:13:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Doing what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.14,0:13:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, this thing we did last year! \NWasn't it fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.01,0:13:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I forgot to tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.50,0:13:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me? \NWhat are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.86,0:13:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what's wrong with you? \NHave you forgotten already?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.01,0:13:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! You mean {\i1}this{\i0} thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.91,0:13:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to stop, \Nwe're not children anymore. {/stopped doing it, such childish thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.51,0:13:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thinking, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.02,0:14:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What was it, Luise? \NWhat did you do last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.45,0:14:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A magnum opus! She brought in some fireworks \Nand set them on fire right behind the counselors! {unsure it's kessaku - masterpiece; best work}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.39,0:14:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They soared up with a {\i1}whoosh!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.76,0:14:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein Ulrica was so scared, \Nshe shrieked and fell off her chair! {/jumped}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.76,0:14:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? That much?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.33,0:14:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a pity I had to leave for home early last year! {/earlier than everyone}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.22,0:14:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying for a day longer \Nwas worth that kind of show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.77,0:14:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, we're starting to draw the numbers! {/lottery}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.32,0:14:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come closer. {/gather}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.47,0:14:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.48,0:14:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They are my favorite! \NSuch roller skates are all the rage these days! {/I want them, those latest style/fashion/state of the art ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.86,0:14:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born to win them today! {/will totally win/get them - no clue what's this itodoru, would assume to get; to obtain; to acquire; to win; to receive; to earn; to take (e.g. a vacation)}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.93,0:14:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,First set - an eraser and a pencil. \NSeven sets in total. {no clue what is nanatou}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.32,0:14:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, person with a number 33.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.19,0:14:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?! Me? Out in the very first round... {/immediately/suddenly I'm out/no longer in the game}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.76,0:14:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,See? What did I tell you before?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.53,0:14:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, person with number 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.26,0:14:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! Now it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.08,0:14:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Next are 10, 5, 29, 11, 3, 15, 35...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.24,0:14:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Four letter sets - 32, 4, 13, 7. {yon tou XXXsetto - would assume "レターセット" whatever it may be}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.38,0:14:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.07,0:14:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.19,0:15:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad! \NWe'll write a million of letters!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.51,0:15:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.78,0:15:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You have become so close, \Neven the fate now binds you two together. {act. "because two are all together; in a body; en masse; all alike​, really getting along"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.66,0:15:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! The first prize, roller skates \Ngo to number 23!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.99,0:15:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Who has number 23?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.23,0:15:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you have that number?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.49,0:15:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I got my prize already.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.66,0:15:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.22,0:15:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.40,0:15:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How odd. Did we forget to give someone number 23?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.60,0:15:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Number 23, congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.41,0:15:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all yours, Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.31,0:15:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ehh. You couldn't have chosen a winner more unfit \Nfor something requiring a physical exercise. {/it fell on the person with the most dull reflexes/least fit of all}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.49,0:15:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be saying things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.63,0:15:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.63,0:15:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When papa and mama \Nare breaking up behind her back,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.00,0:15:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,this would at least provide some distraction \Nso I guess it's a fitting prize. {/with this, she'll be able to forget for a while, so it can't be helped/it's a good consolation prize}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.27,0:15:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Christine!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.68,0:16:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise is doing it again...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.44,0:16:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to slap you, but... {/I'm sorry ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.38,0:16:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But you should apologize!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.72,0:16:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.19,0:16:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.30,0:16:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, Stephie! \NYour happiness is our concern, too. {lit: to be lucky; to be in luck/to be attached; to have; to be included; to come with; to contain; to be in a state​ - no clue how they can be lucky so would assume she means "cheer up so we could be happy for you too"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.30,0:16:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! I'm sure things will start looking up soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.50,0:16:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Our hopes are with you, Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.60,0:16:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Christine? \NYou hope for her happiness too, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.89,0:16:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie, you heard how hard Luise just slapped me - \Nthat's how hard I will be hoping for your well-being. {lit: me share of being beaten by louise, will root for you with all my might, do your best - I think she means either "I'll be cheering for you just as hard as louise slapped me" or "louise's slap made me see ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.64,0:16:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't lose hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.04,0:16:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Christine...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.21,0:16:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What a convoluted way to put it. {/strange encouragement/rooting - this confirms last line was some sort of a joke}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.15,0:16:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly convoluted! {I think, maybe this is a callback to episode 1 when she said "say something more convoluted..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.69,0:17:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Lotte. When you slapped Christine just now, \Nwas it to live up to the character? {lit: fault of becoming me}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.74,0:17:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.31,0:17:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I only knew back then - \Nit hurts Stephie to hear something like that {/I thought you can't say such things to ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.04,0:17:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and before I knew it, \NI slapped her. {/by the time I realized, the slap was already done}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.63,0:17:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a minute, mom. \NI'll get you dinner in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.54,0:17:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Pot, please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.95,0:17:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom is starving after the work! \NPlease, come back! {/return}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.10,0:17:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Pot...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.70,0:18:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.92,0:18:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.11,0:18:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the omelette!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.90,0:18:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you, Herr Omelette. \NNo! Don't come near!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.39,0:18:35.36,Sign,,0,0,0,,Egern Station {would assume https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rottach-Egern even though it doesn't have a train station irl}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.48,0:18:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No way, Luise. I don't think \NI'll ever be able to make a convincing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.57,0:19:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte! Make sure to write to me from Munich!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.56,0:19:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. You too, Truda.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.60,0:19:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, you, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.62,0:19:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,For the next time we meet, \Nlet's try to bring each other some good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.37,0:19:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I trust you to take care of mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.93,0:19:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, we'll meet again soon enough. {/and then, when we're together again}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.58,0:19:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be waiting for you next year!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.26,0:19:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.68,0:19:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Seebühl Village.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.49,0:19:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, my summer vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.89,0:19:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The two embarked on a journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.10,0:19:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise had become Lotte,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.82,0:19:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay with her mother in Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.76,0:20:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But Lotte also had become Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.65,0:20:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, she'll be living with her father in Vienna.
